<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="149" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="20.[89,1295,727,1628]" pageId="20" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[90,445,1398,1431]" pageId="20" pageNumber="149">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. This assessment is based on the fact that although Pine’s Opossum is known only from the holotype, it is likely to be found in a wider area. Known locality is within a protected area (Manu National Park and Biosphere Reserve), and other potential distributional areas are not under high conservation threat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
